  "prompt": "How many thoughts do we have per day?",
  "response": "The idea that humans have a specific number of thoughts per day is hard to quantify precisely, and estimates can vary widely. Some popular claims suggest that an average person has around 60,000 to 80,000 thoughts per day. However, this figure is often viewed with skepticism and is not based on rigorous scientific measurement.\n\nWhat is more accurate is the understanding that the brain is constantly processing information, and thoughts can arise rapidly and continuously throughout the day. The nature of thoughts\u2014ranging from fleeting subconscious impressions to more deliberate and intentional reflections\u2014makes it challenging to define or count them in a straightforward way.\n\nUltimately, while exact numbers are dubious, it is clear that our minds are busy, with continual streams of thoughts throughout our waking hours.",
